9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 259, L.D. 405, “An Act to Define
10 "Solitary Confinement" for the Laws Governing Jails and Correctional Facilities”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Require Reporting on the Uses of Prisoner Segregation'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §1660, sub-§5 is enacted to read:
16 5. Information on segregation. The report must include the following information
17 for county jails and regional jails about prisoners who have been segregated and not
18 allowed to leave their cells for a minimum of 22 hours out of a 24-hour period during the
19 prior calendar year:
20 A. The total number of prisoners who were segregated;
21 B. For each instance of segregation, the total amount of time a prisoner was segregated;
22 and
23 C. The reason why the prisoner was segregated.
24 As used in this subsection, "segregation" means the separation of a prisoner from the
25 general population of a county jail or regional jail for administrative or punitive reasons.
26 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §1660, as amended by PL 2015, c. 315, §3, is further amended
27 by enacting at the end a new paragraph to read:
28 After reviewing the report, the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
29 jurisdiction over criminal justice matters is authorized to submit legislation to address
30 issues raised by the report.
31 Sec. 3. 34-A MRSA §1402, sub-§15 is enacted to read:
32 15. Report on segregated prisoners. On or before January 15, 2026 and annually
33 thereafter, the commissioner shall submit a report to the joint standing committee of the
