COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 259, L.D. 405
314 Legislature having jurisdiction over criminal justice matters that includes the following
325 information for each correctional facility about prisoners who have been segregated and
336 not allowed to leave their cells for a minimum of 22 hours out of a 24-hour period during
347 the prior calendar year:
5 A. The total number of prisoners who were segregated;
6 B. For each instance of segregation, the total amount of time a prisoner was segregated;
7 and
8 C. The reason why the prisoner was segregated.
9 After reviewing the report, the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
10 jurisdiction over criminal justice matters is authorized to submit legislation to address
11 issues raised by the report.'
12 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
13 number to read consecutively.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
1166 changes the title. The amendment requires the Commissioner of Corrections to report
1177 instances of segregation in which a prisoner is segregated and not allowed to leave their
1188 cell for a minimum of 22 hours within a 24-hour period in a correctional facility, county
1199 jail or regional jail, to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
2200 over criminal justice matters. This report must include the total number of prisoners who
2211 were segregated, the total amount of time a prisoner was segregated for each instance of
2222 segregation and the reason why the prisoner was segregated. After reviewing the report,
2233 the joint standing committee is authorized to submit legislation to address issues raised by
2244 the report.
2255 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
